{{en/Community/Junctionary/Navigation}}
This junction is pretty easy to make, but is not complete and trains can get lost.  Trains can go from NW to SW and SE to NE, but can not return.

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/3.4ths junction.png|center|frame|3/4ths junction]]

===Pros===
*Cheap
*Small
*Slope only in the one way of railway
*Useful for fast, serial construction
*Trains in line direction are not slowed, or slowed only a bit and are not blocked themselves
*Easy to remember

===Cons===
*Trains arriving from northeast or southwest are unable to turn left.
*There are merges before splits, which can cause traffic jams.
*One way of railway have to climb slope

